    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-01-22</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-02-22T12:13:27Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Stop Greenlighting Driver Licenses for Illegal Immigrants Act</b> <b>of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill prohibits a state from receiving certain federal law enforcement grants if it takes certain immigration-related actions. Specifically, a state may not receive such grants if it (1) issues a driver license to an individual who does not have proof of U.S. citizenship or lawful presence in the United States, or (2) prohibits a local or state government entity or official from sharing immigration enforcement information with the Department of Homeland Security.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
